> Please note that this recipe may be packaged with samples that contain peanuts and soy.

Wash and dry all produce. Heat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees. Combine
@bulgur wheat{1%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 2 1/2 cups water, and a
pinch of @salt{pinch} in a #medium pot{}. Bring to a boil, reduce to a simmer,
and cover. Cook until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. Remove from heat and keep
covered.

Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{2} into ½-inch wedges. Quarter
@roma tomato{2} through stem end. Halve @zucchini{2} lengthwise and slice into
2-inch wedges. Toss veggies on a #baking sheet{} with 4 tsp @olive oil{8%tsp},
@sumac{2%tsp}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Broil (or roast) until
softened and slightly charred, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Lightly mix @ground beef{16%oz}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup},
@Middle Eastern spice blend{2%tbsp}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch} in a
#large bowl{} to combine. Gently pat into golf-ball-sized meatballs with your
hands.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
meatballs and cook to desired doneness, ~{6-10%minutes}, turning to brown on
all sides.

Finely chop @parsley{1/2%oz}. Fluff bulgur with a #fork{}, season with
@salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}, and stir in half the parsley.

Divide bulgur between plates. Top with veggies and meatballs. Dollop with
@sour cream{4%tbsp} and garnish with remaining parsley.